{
  "stem": "1895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the way to prevent re-settlement or deportation was to get an essential job with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The idea was if you get a war-essential job with the Germans, that you could remain and so could your family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On this basis, my brother Eli and I enlisted and went to work for-- in a munitions factory in Radom.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What is more important for a war industry than munitions?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we went to work hoping that with this job, we will prevent them from resetting or deporting our family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, nothing could be further from the truth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just a ruse, and one of many the Germans used on us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the next thing that I knew-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my brother worked the day shift.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I worked the night shift.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We worked a 12-hour shift.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In this munitions factory in Radom.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, you know, Radom had been set up with two ghettos, one-- two areas.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was called Glinice, which had about 10,000 Jews in it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one was called Walowa in another part of town where we lived, which had about 25,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One day when we were finished with the night shift work, and it was about after 6:00 in the morning, about 6:30, we were ready to be escorted back into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were escorted with Ukrainian black-uniformed guards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All of a sudden, we found that there was a lot of shooting coming from the area of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the guards themselves became confused as to what to do, because they realized that there's something going on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, anyway, that night, which was August 5th, 1942, they had cleaned out the 10,000 Jews of the ghetto Glinice completely.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
